Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.TestScript.setup.action.assert` for use in FHIR R4

0.0.1-snapshot-3
Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-TestScript.setup.action.assert Version:
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-10 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionTestScript_Setup_Action_Assert

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element TestScript.setup.action.assert for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Extension.extension

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • This Extension is not used by any profiles in this Implementation Guide

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element TestScript.setup.action.assert for use in FHIR R4.

  • label: string: The label would be used for tracking/logging purposes by test engines.
  • description: string: The description would be used by test engines for tracking and reporting purposes.
  • direction: code: The direction to use for the assertion.
  • compareToSourceId: string: Id of the source fixture used as the contents to be evaluated by either the "source/expression" or "sourceId/path" definition.
  • compareToSourceExpression: string: The FHIRPath expression for a specific value to evaluate against the source fixture. When compareToSourceId is defined, either compareToSourceExpression or compareToSourcePath must be defined, but not both.
  • compareToSourcePath: string: XPath or JSONPath expression to evaluate against the source fixture. When compareToSourceId is defined, either compareToSourceExpression or compareToSourcePath must be defined, but not both.
  • contentType: code: The mime-type contents to compare against the request or response message 'Content-Type' header.
  • defaultManualCompletion: code: The default manual completion outcome applied to this assertion.
  • expression: string: The FHIRPath expression to be evaluated against the request or response message contents - HTTP headers and payload.
  • headerField: string: The HTTP header field name e.g. 'Location'.
  • minimumId: string: The ID of a fixture. Asserts that the response contains at a minimum the fixture specified by minimumId.
  • navigationLinks: boolean: Whether or not the test execution performs validation on the bundle navigation links.
  • operator: code: The operator type defines the conditional behavior of the assert.
  • path: string: The XPath or JSONPath expression to be evaluated against the fixture representing the response received from server.
  • requestMethod: code: The request method or HTTP operation code to compare against that used by the client system under test.
  • requestURL: string: The value to use in a comparison against the request URL path string.
  • resource: uri: The type of the resource. See the resource list.
  • response: code: continue | switchingProtocols | okay | created | accepted | nonAuthoritativeInformation | noContent | resetContent | partialContent | multipleChoices | movedPermanently | found | seeOther | notModified | useProxy | temporaryRedirect | permanentRedirect | badRequest | unauthorized | paymentRequired | forbidden | notFound | methodNotAllowed | notAcceptable | proxyAuthenticationRequired | requestTimeout | conflict | gone | lengthRequired | preconditionFailed | contentTooLarge | uriTooLong | unsupportedMediaType | rangeNotSatisfiable | expectationFailed | misdirectedRequest | unprocessableContent | upgradeRequired | internalServerError | notImplemented | badGateway | serviceUnavailable | gatewayTimeout | httpVersionNotSupported.
  • responseCode: string: The value of the HTTP response code to be tested.
  • sourceId: id: Fixture to evaluate the XPath/JSONPath expression or the headerField against.
  • stopTestOnFail: boolean: Whether or not the current test execution will stop on failure for this assert.
  • validateProfileId: id: The ID of the Profile to validate against.
  • value: string: The value to compare to.
  • warningOnly: boolean: Whether or not the test execution will produce a warning only on error for this assert.
  • link: uri, canonical: Link or reference providing traceability to the testing requirement for this test.

Maturity: 0

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element TestScript.setup.action.assert for use in FHIR R4.

  • label: string: The label would be used for tracking/logging purposes by test engines.
  • description: string: The description would be used by test engines for tracking and reporting purposes.
  • direction: code: The direction to use for the assertion.
  • compareToSourceId: string: Id of the source fixture used as the contents to be evaluated by either the "source/expression" or "sourceId/path" definition.
  • compareToSourceExpression: string: The FHIRPath expression for a specific value to evaluate against the source fixture. When compareToSourceId is defined, either compareToSourceExpression or compareToSourcePath must be defined, but not both.
  • compareToSourcePath: string: XPath or JSONPath expression to evaluate against the source fixture. When compareToSourceId is defined, either compareToSourceExpression or compareToSourcePath must be defined, but not both.
  • contentType: code: The mime-type contents to compare against the request or response message 'Content-Type' header.
  • defaultManualCompletion: code: The default manual completion outcome applied to this assertion.
  • expression: string: The FHIRPath expression to be evaluated against the request or response message contents - HTTP headers and payload.
  • headerField: string: The HTTP header field name e.g. 'Location'.
  • minimumId: string: The ID of a fixture. Asserts that the response contains at a minimum the fixture specified by minimumId.
  • navigationLinks: boolean: Whether or not the test execution performs validation on the bundle navigation links.
  • operator: code: The operator type defines the conditional behavior of the assert.
  • path: string: The XPath or JSONPath expression to be evaluated against the fixture representing the response received from server.
  • requestMethod: code: The request method or HTTP operation code to compare against that used by the client system under test.
  • requestURL: string: The value to use in a comparison against the request URL path string.
  • resource: uri: The type of the resource. See the resource list.
  • response: code: continue | switchingProtocols | okay | created | accepted | nonAuthoritativeInformation | noContent | resetContent | partialContent | multipleChoices | movedPermanently | found | seeOther | notModified | useProxy | temporaryRedirect | permanentRedirect | badRequest | unauthorized | paymentRequired | forbidden | notFound | methodNotAllowed | notAcceptable | proxyAuthenticationRequired | requestTimeout | conflict | gone | lengthRequired | preconditionFailed | contentTooLarge | uriTooLong | unsupportedMediaType | rangeNotSatisfiable | expectationFailed | misdirectedRequest | unprocessableContent | upgradeRequired | internalServerError | notImplemented | badGateway | serviceUnavailable | gatewayTimeout | httpVersionNotSupported.
  • responseCode: string: The value of the HTTP response code to be tested.
  • sourceId: id: Fixture to evaluate the XPath/JSONPath expression or the headerField against.
  • stopTestOnFail: boolean: Whether or not the current test execution will stop on failure for this assert.
  • validateProfileId: id: The ID of the Profile to validate against.
  • value: string: The value to compare to.
  • warningOnly: boolean: Whether or not the test execution will produce a warning only on error for this assert.
  • link: uri, canonical: Link or reference providing traceability to the testing requirement for this test.

Maturity: 0
